cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with gaze estimation using appearance-based CNN methods. It also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to improve user experience. The proposed training scheme and metric for robustness can be considered as machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories, respectively. Additionally, the use of adversarial training can be related to robotics (cs.RO) as it involves improving the performance of a system in the presence of disturbances.
